text: Riding in my homie's car through the middle of nothing with a dead battery, I have to push the car to second gear using my Bulgarian horsepower to start it, driving with no lights, no blinkers and sticking hands out the windows for turn signals, it dies on every stop, hard pump

Finally it died so it would not start no matter how hard I pushed, some local guy dragged us to a repair shop with his jeep, mechanic had thick small town accent, fixed it up because by luck he had the broken part, drank a shitton of 0.50 $ Kosovan energy drinks at some store
I don't see a curve.

One thing I found strangely touching was how Moshe Dayan would tear up and isolate himself at home because he found people staring at his missing eye intolerable. We can be brave, cruel, irresponsible, but the most vain and cosmetic type of matter still hurts, controls our lives.

You can indiscriminately order the deaths of others, risk your own life over little, play around with life and death at all times, etc., yet people staring at your eyepatch on the street crushes you and makes you want to hide from everything
